The paper proposes a model for learning and updating the autonomy of semi-autonomous systems, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The model also takes into account the proficiency of the system at different levels of autonomy, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the cost of human assistance, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
